<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="1040" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1040">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/3546.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at
                                    Chihuahua</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Chihuahua</hi></placeName>. <lb/> ([<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-10">undated</date>;] Received
                                April 10, 1912—2.30 p.m.)</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Parral taken 4th instant without struggle by rebels, Villa retreating.
                            Violence prevailed; none was respected. Americans suffered less than
                            other foreigners. Salazar commanded rebels. I suggest that occurrences
                            at Parral, which will circulate among Americans here, offer reason for
                            quiet suggestions from this office to Americans to leave as fast as may
                            be consistent with good order. Request instructions as to discreet steps
                            this direction.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Letcher.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>